This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump, Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel, Foreign Minister Abdullah bin Zayed of the United Arab Emirates, and Foreign Minister Abdullatif Al Zayani of Bahrain during a historic peace agreement signing ceremony at the White House. The leaders praised the signing of the Abraham Accords, which mark the first peace deals between Israel and Arab states in over 25 years. They emphasized the significance of these agreements in promoting peace, cooperation, and prosperity in the Middle East. The leaders also expressed gratitude to those involved in the negotiations and highlighted the potential for additional countries to join the peace process. They stressed the importance of choosing cooperation over conflict, and the positive impact these agreements will have on the region.